<doc id="251161" wikidata="Q816153" url="?curid=251161" title="Beloved Isle Cayman">
<text>&quot;Beloved Isle Cayman&quot; is the official national song of the Cayman Islands, composed by Leila Ross-Shier in 1930. It became the official national song when the Cayman Islands Coat of Arms, Flag and National Song Law was passed in 1993.

As a British Overseas Territory, the official national anthem is &quot;God Save the King&quot;.

